review_blob:
There is nothing better than playing some outdoor hockey in the freezing winter here in North Dakota, and kicking back a couple of these while warming up in a shotty wooden warming house covered in graffitti (Manvel, ND).

Good beer, good price, good game.

Six of these, and you will be wishing you hadnt had six of these.

Decent for the price, but not worth the price you pay with your bodily functions.
Reminds me of something by Heineken, with a more pungent aroma.  Dont let that fool you though, this beer is good for the price, and well worth it.
Very solid pale ale.  Good flavor, aroma.  Excellent to use with cooking, and drinking.
Great red, in the vein of Killians, but with much more flavor/palate.  Excellent with a good steak.
